reviews.text: The ingredients used in the rojaks are really fresh. The lady boss and her husband are very friendly! If you are intending to try more than 1 type of rojak from here, do start with the Fruit Rojak with Yuzu sauce. It is super refreshing and will definitely help to whip up your appetite for more plates.

Very nice and fresh Rojak, with very nice auntie and uncle. Heavily recommend!

So far this is the best rojok I have had in the east.  Ingredients are generous and so is the peanut! I specially like the you tiao is extremely crispy!! So far I have not eaten any Rojak that has so crispy you tiao. You tiao is the soul of the rojak, it definitely has to be the best in every rojak! Of cos follow by the sauce, it also must have wow factor for me. Which this stall has it!

I am staying very near ..but never had the chance to try this rojak stall, until recently. I bought the rojak for twice since last week. Like the crispy Youtiao, taupo, fragrant of the "rojak"flower, with generous portion of "heigor.. fresh chili paste and assam water I think...The lady boss was also very nice and flexible and accommodating to my request.
